We are deprecating workspaces in favour of organizations, and moving from project-based to organization-based billing.

## Deprecating workspaces in favor of organizations

We introduced the concept of Workspaces when we launched Nhost V2. We are now moving back to Organizations to be better aligned with our customers and with the rest of the industry. Naming is hard!

Organizations, like workspaces, are a way to group projects together, and they may have multiple members.

Your existing workspaces will be available in the Dashboard for a while but you won't be able to edit them nor create new ones. You will have to migrate your workspaces to organizations with a few clicks. More on this soon. 
 
## Moving from project-based to organization-based billing

Until now, every Nhost project had its own plan, subscription, and addons. Many of you have shared your frustation with the number of invoices involved, and how confusing billing can become, if you have multiple projects.

To address this and simplify billing, we're moving the plan and subscription to the organization instead. Each organization has a plan (starter, pro, team, or enterprise) and all project addons such [Compute Resources](https://docs.nhost.io/compute-resources), [Graphite](https://docs.nhost.io/product/ai), or [Custom Domains](https://docs.nhost.io/platform/custom-domains) are added to the organization subscription they belong to.

### Features & Limits per organization

Features and quotas will be shared across your entire organization. Independent of how many projects you launch, your included quota stays the same. For billing purposes, we sum the usage across all projects in a single, monthly invoice.

As the plan is set for your entire organization, upgrading your organization to a paid plan means that you unlock the benefits of the paid plan for all projects inside your organizations. For example, if you upgrade to the Pro Plan you get email support for every project inside that org rather than just a single project.

You can launch as many organizations as you want. For example, you can create two organizations on the Pro Plan for $25 each and launch a single project in each. This provides the same quotas and pricing that you'd receive today. Importantly, each subsequent database inside that Organization will cost $0.01344/hour (roughly $10 per month), rather than $25.

Read more about quotas and Organization-based Billing including examples in our docs.


## Starter Plan/Organization

Only one starter organization is allowed. Organizations one the starter plan can only have one member. 




